import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].hist()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Effect_Amount_of_damage?")
    plt.xlabel("Effect_Amount_of_damage")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    species_count.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the most common Wildlife_Species involved in strikes?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
